    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-06-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="673"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d673">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Riddle</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-06-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Riddle reports that the Russian minister for foreign affairs requests that
                    the minister of the United States to China communicate to the Russian minister
                    to China the demands of the United States <pb facs="0797" n="711"
                        xml:id="pg_711"/> relative to localities to be opened to trade, and promises
                    that the minister of Russia will be authorized to reply frankly to the minister
                    of the United States and the Chinese Government what the attitude of the Russian
                    Government is. The minister for foreign affairs states to Mr. Riddle that
                    because of the distance, and without knowing what localities are meant, he can
                    not blindly commit himself, as he admits there are some ports whose opening
                    Russia would not favor before the Russian evacuation of Manchuria under
                    satisfactory guaranties is completed.</p>
                <p>A frank interchange of views between the two ministers at Peking is recommended
                    by the minister for foreign affairs.)</p>
            </div>
